<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2179: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-06T17:00:00-03:00">April 6, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 6—4:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. Department’s 33, April 4, 6 p.m. Foreign Office will telegraph
                            informal statement as to present situation to Brazilian representative
                            at Geneva. It points out that this cannot be considered as official
                            inasmuch as the Brazilian Government has no connection with the
                            negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>